title: For Sale/Trade:  STAR model "B" 9X19 mm Handgun
postcontent:
STAR model B 9mm pistol for sale. Purchased new/imported but barely used. Looked up the markings more than likely made in the 1930s and used by the German police. Has some small blemishes here and there but overall a nice gun still. 

These were Spanish made and then imported into Germany.. after the war they were surplussed and stockpiled by Russia. THen imported to the US for sale as a plinker or collector.

The factory original ejector cracked on the spur/tooth part. This is a common failing from Russian arsenals replacing parts with softer steel. Needs a new ejector. Will still cycle but jams. Still have the original ejector. Have some tool steel that I was going to machine a new ejector out of but never got around to it and don't have time (will include). Also new ejectors can be ordered online for around $30. Everything else functions like new.

If that same photo in their listing is also in gunbroker, it is very likely they are scam artist. Flag the posting right away and do us all a favor

You can also look at the listing description, take a few sentences and look it up on google, if google returns that the description from a past listing, highly likely they are scam artists. Also the one thing that screws it up for all of them is that they are lazy, they won't take the time to actually make a good description, sometimes they just put $1 or maybe hardly nothing in the description, those guys did us service that we can easily flag their listing.

These low life POS scam artists use a google phone numbers and some of them have claimed to be from Indonesia and Nigeria. They also have weird emails. Sometimes the name they give you is not a very common American name like "Bingham" or some other BS name. Also look at their English grammar, if its bad, they are most likely scam artists

All you scam artists, I hope one day karma catches up to you.
